definition.value: A alpha,omega-dicarboxylic acid that is azelaic acid substituted by amino groups at positions 2 and 6.
A monohydroxybenzoic acid that is 4-hydroxybenzoic acid carrying an additional amino substitutent at position 3.
A macrolide antibiotic that is tylactone having a beta-D-mycaminosyl residue attached at position 5.
A cyclic peptide antibiotic produced by a strain of Streptomyces toyocaensis.
A monohydroxybenzoic acid that is 3-hydroxybenzoic acid carrying an additional amino substitutent at position 4.
A macrolide antibiotic useful for the treatment of bacterial infections.
A semisynthetic penicillin antibiotic used in treating infections caused by Pseudomonas aeruginosa, Escherichia coli, and Haemophilus influenzae.
A macrolide antibiotic that is tylonolide having 6-deoxy-beta-D-allopyranosyl and  beta-D-mycaminosyl residues attached to two of its hydroxy groups..
A twelve-membered macrolide antibiotic that is biosynthesised by Streptomyces venezuelae.
A macrolide antibiotic that is narbonolide having a 3,4,6-trideoxy-3-(dimethylamino)-beta-D-xylo-hexopyranosyl residue attached at position 6. It is biosynthesised by Streptomyces venezuelae.
A twelve-membered macrolide antibiotic that is biosynthesised by Streptomyces venezuelae.
A macrolide antibiotic that is biosynthesised by Streptomyces venezuelae.
A member of the class of rifamycins that exhibits antibiotic and antitubercular properties.
An inoganic sodium salt with formula with formula NaAsO2.
A penicillanic acid ester that is the 1-ethoxycarbonyloxyethyl ester of ampicillin. It is a semi-synthetic, microbiologically inactive prodrug of ampicillin.
A member of the class of benzoic acids that is benzoic acid substituted by methoxy groups at positions 2 and 3.
A homodetic cyclic decapeptide consisting of D-Phe, L-Pro, L-Phe, D-Phe, L-Asn, L-Gln, L-Tyr, L-Val, L-Orn, and L-Leu residues coupled in sequence and cyclised head-to-tail.
A macrolide antibiotic that is the 3,4,6-trideoxy-3-(dimethylamino)-beta-D-xylo-hexoside of 10-deoxymethynolide.
A monocarboxylic acid anion obtained by the deprotonation of the carboxy group of ferulic acid.
A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid that is pyruvic acid substituted by a 1H-indol-3-yl group at position 3. It has been found in Lycopersicon esculentum
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is acetate where the methyl group has been hydroxylated.
A C4-dicarboxylate that is the E-isomer of but-2-enedioate(2-)
